When addressing the first problem, it is worth noting that our main dependent variable has 57 categories. A number of simulation studies have shown that when the number of ordered categories is relatively high (i.e., five or more), the dependent variable can be treated as continuous without significant losses in terms of the statistical properties of the estimates [26–28]. Therefore, linear models such as OLS provide accurate estimates in many situations. Even so, in addition to the linear model in Eq. (1), we also estimate an ordered multinomial response model [29]. The model assumes that there is an unobserved latent outcome variable y* [30]:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
