With respect to the non-random nature of the sample, a non-representative sample leads to biased estimates if sample selection is the result of unobservable characteristics that are associated with both participation and outcomes. Since individuals had to first apply and then travel to campus to participate in the study, it is plausible that SPOH and individual choice of whether or not to participate are correlated. We use a two-equation procedure to correct for potential sample selection bias. That is, we also estimate an equation that models participation in the sample:5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
